rowhammer (0.18.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add a lock delay: a piece that lands is no longer locked immediately
    but rests for a short grace window (LOCK_DELAY_MS, 250 ms), during
    which it can still be moved left/right or rotated. The touchdown timer
    is only reset when a move makes the piece airborne again; a move that
    leaves it resting keeps the original deadline, so a piece cannot be
    stalled forever on the floor. Hard drop still locks instantly, and the
    delay does not run while paused or in the pause menu.

 -- roemer2201 <r.oliver@web.de>  Wed, 22 Jul 2026 13:00:00 +0200

rowhammer (0.17.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add a per-round play-time counter: the HUD shows the running round's
    elapsed time (MM:SS, paused and pause-menu time excluded) and each
    highscore entry now stores and displays that play time. The highscore
    line format gains a trailing "time" field (seconds).

 -- roemer2201 <r.oliver@web.de>  Wed, 22 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

rowhammer (0.16.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Sync packaging with the current game (0.16.x): the main script is now
    rowhammer.sh and the wonder ASCII art in assets/wonders/ is installed
    alongside the library modules.
  * Reapply the symlink resolution for SCRIPT_DIR in rowhammer.sh so the
    /usr/games/rowhammer launcher finds modules and assets.

 -- roemer2201 <r.oliver@web.de>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0200

rowhammer (0.2.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging (native package).
  * Install the game under /usr/share/rowhammer with a /usr/games/rowhammer
    launcher symlink; tetris.sh now resolves symlinks when locating its
    library modules.

